Since you're preparing for interviews and DSA, don't learn these randomly. Build them in dependency order so each topic helps with the next one.

Phase 1: Tree Basics (Learn First)
Implement a Binary Tree
Program to find the depth of a binary tree
Level Order Traversal
Binary Tree Level Order Traversal (LeetCode 102)
Check if two trees are identical

These teach:

Tree structure
Recursion
Queue (BFS)
Tree traversal patterns
Phase 2: BST Basics
Implement BST with insertion, contains, delete
Find min in BST using recursion
Second largest in BST
Third largest in BST
Kth Smallest Element in a BST (230)
Closest element in BST to target

These teach:

BST properties
Inorder traversal
Searching efficiently
Phase 3: Balanced Trees
Check if tree is balanced
Program to check whether tree is balanced or not
Convert sorted array to balanced BST

These teach:

Height calculations
Divide and conquer
Phase 4: Intermediate Binary Tree Problems
Sum of left leaf nodes
Count single child nodes in BST
Remove duplicates from BT
Check if subtree

These are common interview-style recursion problems.

Phase 5: Advanced / Conceptual
Convert BT to BST
Check if BST is perfect

These require understanding multiple concepts together.

My recommended order for the first 7 problems:
Implement Binary Tree
Find Depth of Binary Tree
Level Order Traversal
Check if Two Trees are Identical
Implement BST (insert, contains)
Find Min in BST
Kth Smallest Element in BST

After these 7, most of the remaining problems will feel much easier.

For MERN/backend interviews, I'd focus first on:

Depth of Tree
Level Order Traversal
BST Insert/Search/Delete
Kth Smallest Element in BST
Check Balanced Tree
Subtree Check

These are asked much more often than "Perfect BST" or "Convert BT to BST."